{
  "abstract": "In 2018–2020, during surveys of approximately 160 ha in\r\n15 cucumber growing locations across the Solan District of\r\nHimachal Pradesh, the crop was found to be infected by a root\r\nand crown rot fungus causing symptoms such as the yellowing\r\nand wilting of leaves in 5–15% of plants. Two–three days\r\nafter the isolations were made from root, crown and stem\r\nportions (Aldakil et al. 2019), in 60% of 40 samples colonies\r\ngrew out that were initially white, aerial and floccose and\r\nlater on turned yellowish to buff brown in colour....",
